<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She has been cast in the celebrity line-up for Dancing With The Stars.</p>

<p>And Chrishell Stause appeared delighted as she arrived at the studio to practice her ballroom skills on Wednesday, ahead of the show's start date next week.</p>

<p>The Selling Sunset star, 39, cut a glamorous figure in a hot pink mini dress with scalloped detailing, which flaunted her toned pins to perfection.</p>

<p>Raring to go: Chrishell Stause appeared delighted as she arrived at the studio to practice her ballroom skills on Wednesday, ahead of the show's start date next week</p>

<p>Chrishell further elongated her legs with a pair of barely-there nude strappy heels, while carrying her dance gear in a gym bag on her shoulder.</p>

<p>The reality star flashed a beaming smile as she enhanced her pretty features with a full face of make-up and wore her highlighted locks in beachy waves.</p>

<p>She ensured she followed state coronavirus guidelines as she arrived equipped with a protective face mask.</p>

<p>Glam: The Selling Sunset star, 39, cut a glamorous figure in a hot pink mini dress with scalloped detailing, which flaunted her toned pins to perfection</p>

<p>Chrishell was later spotted exiting the studio wearing a form-fitting white crop top, teamed with a pair of gym leggings and trainers.</p>

<p>The outing came following the news Derek Hough would be joining the judge's table in lieu of longtime judge Len Goodman.</p>

<p>Derek, 35, was a dancer on the show from 2007 to 2016, winning the coveted MirrorBall trophy a record six times.</p>

<p>Sporty chic: Chrishell was later spotted exiting the studio wearing a form-fitting white crop top, teamed with a pair of gym leggings and trainers</p>

<p>He has since been keeping busy as a judge on NBC's World of Dance alongside Jennifer Lopez and Ne-Yo.</p>

<p>Carrie Ann Inaba and Bruno Tomoli will return to their roles as judges however this season had already gone through several shakeups.</p>

<p>Earlier this summer DWTS decided to ditch hosts Erin Andrews and Tom Bergeron for Tyra Banks.</p>

<p>Season 29 of Dancing With The Stars premieres September 14 on ABC with a special two-hour episode to kick off the season. </p>

